---
/*
  LEARNING NOTE — Single-page stepper (sometimes called a "wizard"):
  The pattern you're using here has a few common names:

  • "Stepper" or "wizard" → in forms and onboarding flows (most accurate here)
  • "Carousel" → when slides swap with a swipe/animation (same JS idea,
     different visual metaphor — usually implies left/right movement)
  • "Multi-step form" → when each step collects data (also accurate here
     because step 1 collects the language preference)

  All three share the same core mechanic: ONE page in the URL,
  JavaScript shows/hides sections and tracks which step you're on.
  "Stepper" is the clearest name for this use case.
*/
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ButtonNext from '../components/ButtonNext.astro';
import ButtonClose from '../components/ButtonClose.astro';
import PolyIcon from '../components/PolyIcon.astro';
---

<Layout title="Welcome" description="Learn how to play The Word">
  <main class="onboarding-screen">

    <div class="bg-shapes" aria-hidden="true">
      <PolyIcon shape="diamond" size={60} color="rgba(219,210,155,0.12)" />
      <PolyIcon shape="pentagon" size={80} color="rgba(219,210,155,0.10)" />
      <PolyIcon shape="hexagon" size={60} color="rgba(219,210,155,0.12)" />
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <p class="step-counter" id="step-counter" aria-live="polite">1/3</p>

      <!-- ── STEP 1 — Language preference ──────────────────── -->
      <section class="step" id="step-1">
        <p class="card-text"
          data-es="Aunque las palabras que te vas a encontrar como objetivo del juego están en inglés, tienes la opción de iniciar con las explicaciones en español y gradualmente cambiar al inglés."
          data-en="The target words in this game are in English. You can choose to start with instructions in Spanish and gradually transition to English, or go fully English from the start."
        >Aunque las palabras que te vas a encontrar como objetivo del juego están en inglés, tienes la opción de iniciar con las explicaciones en español y gradualmente cambiar al inglés.</p>

        <div class="card-shapes" aria-hidden="true">
          <PolyIcon shape="diamond"  size={42} color="#3a8c5c" />
          <PolyIcon shape="pentagon" size={50} color="#3a8c5c" />
          <PolyIcon shape="hexagon"  size={42} color="#3a8c5c" />
        </div>

        <fieldset class="lang-fieldset">
          <legend class="sr-only">Choose your language</legend>
          <label class="lang-option">
            <input type="radio" name="lang" value="es" checked />
            <span>Prefiero empezar en español.</span>
          </label>
          <label class="lang-option">
            <input type="radio" name="lang" value="en" />
            <span>English, please!</span>
          </label>
        </fieldset>
      </section>

      <!-- ── STEP 2 — Game rules ────────────────────────────── -->
      <section class="step hidden" id="step-2">
        <p class="card-text"
          data-es="-Este juego consiste en descubrir la palabra misteriosa. Hay 3 categorías:"
          data-en="-This game is about finding out the mysterious word. There are 3 categories:"
        >-This game is about finding out the mysterious word. There are 3 categories:</p>

        <ul class="category-list">
          <li>
            <PolyIcon shape="diamond"  size={18} color="var(--color-accent)" />
            <span data-es="- palabras de 4 letras." data-en="- 4 letter words.">- 4 letter words.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <PolyIcon shape="pentagon" size={18} color="var(--color-accent)" />
            <span data-es="- palabras de 5 letras." data-en="- 5 letter words.">- 5 letter words.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <PolyIcon shape="hexagon"  size={18} color="var(--color-accent)" />
            <span data-es="- palabras de 6 letras." data-en="- 6 letter words.">- 6 letter words.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="card-text"
          data-es="-Solo tienes 5 oportunidades para adivinar la palabra correcta. Hay solo 1 palabra por categoría al día."
          data-en="-You only have 5 opportunities to guess the correct word. There is only 1 word per category per day."
        >-You only have 5 opportunities to guess the correct word. There is only 1 word per category per day.</p>

        <p class="card-text"
          data-es="-Entre más letras, más complicada puede ser la palabra. ¡Aun así, te animamos a jugar las 3 categorías diariamente!"
          data-en="-The larger the number of letters, the more complicated the word could be. Yet, we encourage you to play the 3 categories daily!"
        >-The larger the number of letters, the more complicated the word could be. Yet, we encourage you to play the 3 categories daily!</p>
      </section>

      <!-- ── STEP 3 — Rewards ───────────────────────────────── -->
      <section class="step hidden" id="step-3">
        <p class="card-text"
          data-es="-Ya sea que hayas descubierto la palabra del día o hayas perdido, tu recompensa es la traducción, etimología y usos de la palabra, y un +1 en tu contador de puntaje."
          data-en="-Either if you found out the word of the day or you lost, your reward is the translation, etymology and uses for the word, and a +1 in your score counter for the category you're playing in."
        >-Either if you found out the word of the day or you lost, your reward is the translation, etymology and uses for the word, and a +1 in your score counter for the category you're playing in.</p>

        <p class="card-text"
          data-es="-Por ahora este puntaje solo sirve para presumir, pero puede volverse útil en el futuro."
          data-en="-As of right now this score is worth nothing more than showing off, but it may become useful in the future."
        >-As of right now this score is worth nothing more than showing off, but it may become useful in the future.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- ── Footer ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <footer class="card-footer">
        <!--
          "Don't show again" checkbox — only visible on step 3.
          
          LEARNING NOTE — localStorage as user preference storage:
          We save this as a flag in localStorage. Then, at the TOP
          of this page's <script>, we check that flag immediately —
          if it's set, we redirect the user to the index before they
          even see the onboarding. This is how most apps implement
          "skip intro" behaviour without a backend or login system.
        -->
        <label class="dont-show-label hidden" id="dont-show-label">
          <input type="checkbox" id="dont-show-checkbox" />
          <span id="dont-show-text"
            data-es="No mostrar de nuevo."
            data-en="Don't show again."
          >Don't show again.</span>
        </label>

        <div id="btn-next-wrapper">
          <ButtonNext />
        </div>
        <div id="btn-close-wrapper" class="hidden">
          <ButtonClose href="/" />
        </div>
      </footer>
    </div>

  </main>
</Layout>

<script>
  /*
    ── "Don't show again" redirect ─────────────────────────────
    
    LEARNING NOTE — Early redirect pattern:
    This runs BEFORE anything else. If the user already checked
    "don't show again" on a previous visit, we send them straight
    to the index. This is why the check is at the very top of the
    script — we want to bail out as fast as possible.

    window.location.replace() is used instead of window.location.href
    because replace() removes the current page from browser history,
    so the back button won't bring them back to onboarding.
  */
  const SKIP_KEY = 'theword-skip-onboarding';
  const LANG_KEY = 'theword-lang';

  if (localStorage.getItem(SKIP_KEY) === 'true') {
    window.location.replace('/');
  }

  // ── State ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  let currentStep = 1;
  const totalSteps = 3;
  let selectedLang: 'es' | 'en' =
    (localStorage.getItem(LANG_KEY) as 'es' | 'en') ?? 'es';

  // ── Element refs ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  const stepCounter      = document.getElementById('step-counter')!;
  const btnNextWrapper   = document.getElementById('btn-next-wrapper')!;
  const btnCloseWrapper  = document.getElementById('btn-close-wrapper')!;
  const dontShowLabel    = document.getElementById('dont-show-label')!;
  const dontShowCheckbox = document.getElementById('dont-show-checkbox') as HTMLInputElement;
  const dontShowText     = document.getElementById('dont-show-text')!;
  const langRadios       = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLInputElement>('input[name="lang"]');

  // ── Language swap ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  /*
    LEARNING NOTE — querySelectorAll + forEach:
    This grabs every element that has BOTH a data-es and data-en
    attribute, then sets its visible text to whichever language is
    selected. It's a lightweight substitute for a real i18n library.
    "i18n" stands for "internationalization" (18 letters between i–n).
  */
  function applyLanguage(lang: 'es' | 'en') {
    document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('[data-es][data-en]').forEach(el => {
      el.textContent = el.dataset[lang] ?? '';
    });
  }

  // Restore saved language preference
  langRadios.forEach(r => { if (r.value === selectedLang) r.checked = true; });
  applyLanguage(selectedLang);

  langRadios.forEach(radio => {
    radio.addEventListener('change', () => {
      selectedLang = radio.value as 'es' | 'en';
      localStorage.setItem(LANG_KEY, selectedLang);
      applyLanguage(selectedLang);
    });
  });

  // ── "Don't show again" checkbox ───────────────────────────────
  /*
    LEARNING NOTE — Saving a boolean in localStorage:
    localStorage only stores strings, so we save the string 'true'
    and check for it with === 'true' when reading back.
    Alternatively you could use JSON.stringify/parse, but for a
    single boolean the string approach is simplest.
  */
  dontShowCheckbox.addEventListener('change', () => {
    if (dontShowCheckbox.checked) {
      localStorage.setItem(SKIP_KEY, 'true');
    } else {
      localStorage.removeItem(SKIP_KEY);
    }
  });

  // ── Step navigation ───────────────────────────────────────────
  function goToStep(step: number) {
    document.querySelectorAll('.step').forEach(s => s.classList.add('hidden'));
    document.getElementById(`step-${step}`)?.classList.remove('hidden');
    stepCounter.textContent = `${step}/${totalSteps}`;

    const isLast = step === totalSteps;
    btnNextWrapper.classList.toggle('hidden', isLast);
    btnCloseWrapper.classList.toggle('hidden', !isLast);

    /*
      Show the "Don't show again" label only on the final step.
      
      LEARNING NOTE — classList.toggle(className, condition):
      The second argument is a boolean. When true → adds the class.
      When false → removes it. Cleaner than an if/else block.
    */
    dontShowLabel.classList.toggle('hidden', !isLast);

    // Keep the "don't show" text in sync with the current language
    applyLanguage(selectedLang);

    currentStep = step;
  }

  // ── Event delegation ─────────────────────────────────────────
  /*
    LEARNING NOTE — Event delegation:
    Instead of adding a click listener to EACH button, we add ONE
    listener to the whole document. When any element is clicked, we
    walk up the DOM tree with .closest() to find the nearest ancestor
    with a data-action attribute. This handles dynamically-added
    buttons too, and is more memory-efficient than per-element listeners.
  */
  document.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
    const action = (e.target as HTMLElement)
      .closest('[data-action]')
      ?.getAttribute('data-action');

    if (action === 'next-step' && currentStep < totalSteps) {
      goToStep(currentStep + 1);
    }
  });

  // Init on first load
  goToStep(1);
</script>

<style>
  .onboarding-screen {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    position: relative;
  }

  .bg-shapes {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: var(--space-xl);
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .card {
    width: 100%;
    background-color: var(--color-card);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    border: 1.5px solid rgba(219, 210, 155, 0.2);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.35);
    min-height: 420px;
  }

  .step-counter {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: rgba(219, 210, 155, 0.6);
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  }

  .step {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    flex: 1;
  }

  .hidden { display: none !important; }

  .card-text {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-align: justify;
  }

  .card-shapes {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin: var(--space-xs) 0;
  }

  .lang-fieldset {
    border: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .lang-option {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .lang-option input[type="radio"] {
    accent-color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-top: 3px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .category-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
    padding-left: var(--space-md);
  }

  .category-list li {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  /* ── Footer ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .card-footer {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-top: auto;
    padding-top: var(--space-sm);
  }

  /* "Don't show again" label */
  .dont-show-label {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: rgba(219, 210, 155, 0.65);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .dont-show-label input[type="checkbox"] {
    accent-color: var(--color-accent);
    width: 14px;
    height: 14px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .sr-only {
    position: absolute;
    width: 1px; height: 1px;
    padding: 0; margin: -1px;
    overflow: hidden;
    clip: rect(0,0,0,0);
    border: 0;
  }
</style>
